        "execSummary":  "The wave of national sovereign AI programs described here will reshape the enterprise AI landscape: governments purchasing domestic AI infrastructure and insisting on locally-trained models will create new compliance requirements and market fragmentation for multinationals operating across jurisdictions. For enterprise AI strategy leaders, the implication is that a single global AI deployment model may become untenable ΓÇö localization of models, data residency, and compute will increasingly be mandated. Customer-support organizations with international operations should begin auditing which markets are advancing sovereign AI requirements and how that affects their vendor and architecture choices. The article is NVIDIA-centric; the infrastructure investment thesis aligns with NVIDIA\u0027s commercial interests in selling AI factory infrastructure to governments.",
